title: Grateful Dead Live at The Omni on 1991-04-05
description:
Set 1

Shakedown Street, Minglewood Blues, Stagger Lee, Mama Tried-> Mexicali Blues, Friend Of The Devil, Queen Jane Approximately, Deal

Set 2

Iko Iko, Saint Of Circumstance, Terrapin Station-> Stir It Up Jam-> Drums-> Jam-> The Other One-> Wharf Rat-> Throwing Stones-> Not Fade Away, E: The Mighty Quinn

reviews.review_text:
Healy is the MAN This tour was outstanding from the taper section. Healy had PA stacks hanging from the rear corners of the floor making quad sound. Totally epic. Sound was bouncing around the corners from all angles. This show was the pinnacle. OtherOne StirItUp Shakedown and Space Jam were out of this world.
Getting Healy's tape is truly exciting even 27 years later..., thanks a ton.
